{
  "stem": "7458.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had a president by the name of Pilsudski and a premier by the name of Moscicki, both of whom with terrible antisemites.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so the Poles-- the farmers and the peasants-- had blind antisemitism that they really didn't know why, but they knew that the Jews could be used as a scapegoat.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The government did not stop it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In fact, the government supported it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And before you know it, they made it impossible for Jews to get out altogether.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we were locked in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we heard rumors that war was coming to Europe.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we heard, of course, about Hitler and the demands he made on Czechoslovakia and then Austria, the Anschluss.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we heard about Chamberlain and the visit to Munich and the appeasement and all that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We heard that demands were made on Poland, the Danzig area where many Germans lived.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They wanted that annexed to Germany.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we thought all of it would somehow be worked out and settled and that certainly France and England were ready and able to defend themselves and the rest of the countries in Europe against any Nazi-- any German designs.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so we-- we were worried but we were not-- we did not realize the total danger that lay ahead.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In-- on September 1st, 1939, of course, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Germany was attacked from both sides.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We then found-- I mean, Poland was attacked from both sides.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We found out that Hitler and Stalin signed a non-aggression pact, which divided Poland into two halves along a long river that divides Poland in half.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the Germans marched in within a few days.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The Polish army, which consisted of some soldiers riding horses and carrying swords, were certainly no match for the German Blitzkrieg, Panzers, and airplanes, and artillery.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
